A cozy living room at dusk in Studio Ghibli style, featuring two young twin boys sitting cross-legged on a wooden floor, completely absorbed in building an elaborate wooden block tower together. Warm golden light streams through a window where lush green trees are visible outside. The corner where a television would typically sit is notably empty, replaced by a potted plant with trailing vines. Scattered around the children are picture books, crayons, and paper airplanes. A cat curls up nearby watching them play. The room has soft watercolor textures, gentle shadows, and that distinctive Ghibli warmth with detailed but whimsical furniture and subtle dust motes floating in the evening light.
